<answer> We find that 
\begin{align*}7x-3z&=2.\end{align*}
Now, we multiple -3 to both sides, we find that $11x+9z=-6$.
Thus, we have that
\begin{align*}
b&=11x+9z\\
&=-6.
\end{align*}
Solving
\begin{align*}
a-3b&=-3(-6)-7(2)=-6\\
b&=11x+9z=-6.
\end{align*}
Now multipling $9$ to $b$ gives us $9b=9(-6)=-54$. Autumning $9b$ to $a$ gives us $a+9b=-6-54=-60$. Thus subtracting $\textcolor{red}{60}$ to both sides gives us $a+9b-60=\textcolor{red}{-60}$. Thus, we compute
\begin{align*}
28x&=-60\\
x&=-\frac{60}{28}\\
&=-\frac{15}{7} \end{align*}

